commitResults.messageTitle: Implement a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user, simply echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types bye.
Level 2. Add, List Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Level 3. Mark as Done Add the ability to mark tasks as done.
Level 4. ToDos, Events, Deadlines Add support for tracking three types of tasks:
commitResults.messageBody:
1. ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it e.g., visit new theme park
2. Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time e.g., submit report by 11/10/2019 5pm
3. Events: tasks that start at a specific time and ends at a specific time e.g., team project meeting on 2/10/2019 2-4pm

commitResults.messageTitle: A-TextUiTesting Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
Level 5. Handle Errors Teach Duke to deal with errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user.
Level 6. Delete Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
Add case condition for "task" and "tasks" in printing
commitResults.messageBody: Fix the alignment issue for switch

commitResults.messageTitle: Create storage in a text file for loading and saving tasks
Add feature to store deadline dates / time and event dates / time as java.time.LocalDate in task objects.
Add UserInterface makeMsg for array of string.
